  "root_text": {
    "an4.47:0.1": "Aṅguttara Nikāya 4.47 ",
    "an4.47:0.2": "5. Rohitassavagga ",
    "an4.47:0.3": "Suvidūrasutta ",
    "an4.47:1.1": "“Cattārimāni, bhikkhave, suvidūravidūrāni. ",
    "an4.47:1.2": "Katamāni cattāri? ",
    "an4.47:1.3": "Nabhañca, bhikkhave, pathavī ca; ",
    "an4.47:1.4": "idaṁ paṭhamaṁ suvidūravidūre. ",
    "an4.47:1.5": "Orimañca, bhikkhave, tīraṁ samuddassa pārimañca; ",
    "an4.47:1.6": "idaṁ dutiyaṁ suvidūravidūre. ",
    "an4.47:1.7": "Yato ca, bhikkhave, verocano abbhudeti yattha ca atthameti; ",
    "an4.47:1.8": "idaṁ tatiyaṁ suvidūravidūre. ",
    "an4.47:1.9": "Satañca, bhikkhave, dhammo asatañca dhammo; ",
    "an4.47:1.10": "idaṁ catutthaṁ suvidūravidūre. ",
    "an4.47:1.11": "Imāni kho, bhikkhave, cattāri suvidūravidūrānīti. ",
    "an4.47:2.1": "Nabhañca dūre pathavī ca dūre, ",
    "an4.47:2.2": "Pāraṁ samuddassa tadāhu dūre; ",
    "an4.47:2.3": "Yato ca verocano abbhudeti, ",
    "an4.47:2.4": "Pabhaṅkaro yattha ca atthameti; ",
    "an4.47:2.5": "Tato have dūrataraṁ vadanti, ",
    "an4.47:2.6": "Satañca dhammaṁ asatañca dhammaṁ. ",
    "an4.47:3.1": "Abyāyiko hoti sataṁ samāgamo, ",
    "an4.47:3.2": "Yāvāpi tiṭṭheyya tatheva hoti; ",
    "an4.47:3.3": "Khippañhi veti asataṁ samāgamo, ",
    "an4.47:3.4": "Tasmā sataṁ dhammo asabbhi ārakā”ti. ",
    "an4.47:3.5": "Sattamaṁ. "
  },
  "translation_text": {
    "an4.47:0.1": "Numbered Discourses 4.47 ",
    "an4.47:0.2": "5. With Rohitassa ",
    "an4.47:0.3": "Very Far Apart ",
    "an4.47:1.1": "“Mendicants, these four things are very far apart. ",
    "an4.47:1.2": "What four? ",
    "an4.47:1.3": "The firmament and the earth. … ",
    "an4.47:1.4": "",
    "an4.47:1.5": "The near and the far shore of the ocean. … ",
    "an4.47:1.6": "",
    "an4.47:1.7": "Where the sun rises and where it sets. … ",
    "an4.47:1.8": "",
    "an4.47:1.9": "The teaching of the virtuous and the teaching of the wicked. … ",
    "an4.47:1.10": "",
    "an4.47:1.11": "These are the four things very far apart. ",
    "an4.47:2.1": "The firmament is far from the earth; ",
    "an4.47:2.2": "they say the other shore of the ocean is far; ",
    "an4.47:2.3": "and where the sun rises is far ",
    "an4.47:2.4": "from where that beacon sets. ",
    "an4.47:2.5": "But even further apart than that, they say, ",
    "an4.47:2.6": "is the teaching of the virtuous from the wicked. ",
    "an4.47:3.1": "The company of the virtuous is reliable; ",
    "an4.47:3.2": "as long as it remains, it stays the same. ",
    "an4.47:3.3": "But the company of the wicked is fickle, ",
    "an4.47:3.4": "and so the teaching of the virtuous <j>is far from the wicked.” "
  },
  "variant_text": {
    "an4.47:0.3": "Suvidūrasutta → suvidūravidūrasuttaṁ (bj) ",
    "an4.47:1.7": "atthameti → atthaṅgameti (sya-all); veti (mr) ",
    "an4.47:3.2": "Yāvāpi → yāvampi (bj, sya-all, km, pts1ed) "
  },
